<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - CRANKCASE, CRANKSHAFT and BEARINGS, CAMSHAFT and BUSHINGS -
        Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="s26508.3">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcproc id="s26508.3.1" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="1">
            <title>Camshaft Bushings</title>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, use the correct camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding
                        collet).
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Lubricate new camshaft bushings and crankcase bores with clean engine oil.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650831" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd06/D0629.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Installation of cam bushing</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply hole</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Pulling screw</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Backup nut</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing remover/installer (expanding collet)</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Camshaft bushing oil supply hole</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide a new bushing on the Camshaft Bushing Remover/installer (expanding collet) .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Thread pulling screw, backup nut, and Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding
                    collet) together.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten expanding collet by turning backup nut until bushing is securely held on the
                    Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer (expanding collet).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, and to ensure correct oil circulation through the crankcase, make
                        certain camshaft bushing oil holes are aligned with the corresponding oil supply holes in the
                        crankcase.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To aid in alignment of bushing and crankcase oil holes, use a marker to indicate oil
                    hole location on backup nut of installation tool. Repeat this step for each camshaft bushing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install all camshaft bushings through rear of crankcase. Pull bushings in place at rear
                    of crankcase by turning pulling nut on pulling screw. Remove Camshaft Bushing Remover/Installer
                    (expanding collet) and inspect oil hole alignment.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
